The White House has issued a presidential proclamation recognizing Pan American Day and Pan American Week. The proclamation highlights the historical and current bonds of friendship among the nations and people of the Americas. It also acknowledges significant milestones, such as the 80th anniversary of the first Pan American Day Proclamation and the centennial anniversary of the Organization of American States' headquarters. The proclamation emphasizes the commitment of the administration to building strong partnerships in the Americas, focusing on social and economic opportunity, citizen safety, democratic institutions, and clean energy. It also mentions the united response to the earthquakes in Haiti and Chile and the ongoing support for reconstruction efforts. The proclamation concludes by urging the governors and officials of the United States to honor these observances with appropriate ceremonies and activities.